Presentation Title: Project DRISHTI
Digital Refinery Intelligence & Safety Holistic Tracking Initiative Transforming Refineries from Reactive Operations to Predictive Intelligence

Slide 1: Executive Overview & Value Proposition
The Paradigm Shift: Modern refineries are drowning in data but starving for foresight. Currently, operations react to lab results, equipment failures, and pressure surges after they occur. Project DRISHTI introduces a unified, AI-driven control layer that sits above your existing DCS, transforming raw sensor data into prescriptive foresight.

The ROI & Value Delivered:

Maximize Profit Margins: Stop "margin leakage" by operating exactly at the optimal economic point, dynamically adjusted in real-time.
Eliminate Unplanned Downtime: Catch mechanical degradation curves 72 hours before a catastrophic pump or compressor failure.
Safeguard Physical Assets: Protect critical pipelines from devastating weather-related blockages (e.g., Benzene freezing).
Ensure Strict ESG Compliance: Guarantee that you stay below regulatory flare quotas by predicting and mitigating surges before the relief valves ever open.
Slide 2: Module 1 – Yield Optimization (Margin Capture)
The Problem: Traditional lab quality results arrive hours after the product is processed, forcing operators to run highly conservative (sub-optimal) parameters to avoid off-spec products. The AI/ML Architecture:

Model Used: Ensemble Machine Learning (Random Forests & Gradient Boosting).
The Advantage: These models excel at mapping highly non-linear, multi-variable chemical processes far better than traditional linear Advanced Process Controls (APCs).
How it Works: It creates a dynamic 3D response surface—a "Soft Sensor"—to find the absolute optimal tuning sweet spot in real-time. Direct Client Value: Instantly links operational levers (like Furnace Temp) to their exact economic impact, capturing millions in previously lost daily margins without risking product quality.
Slide 3: Module 2 – Predictive Maintenance (Asset Reliability)
The Problem: Unexpected failures of critical rotating equipment (pumps/compressors) force multi-million-dollar outages and require bloated spare parts inventories. The AI/ML Architecture:

Model Used: Time-Series Anomaly Detection and Clustering Algorithms (Autoencoders, DBSCAN).
The Advantage: Instead of relying on generic manufacturer thresholds, these models learn the unique "normal" baseline vibration/heat signature for every individual machine.
How it Works: It flags subtle degradation curves 48 to 72 hours prior to a catastrophic mechanical failure. Direct Client Value: Shifts maintenance from "schedule-based" to "condition-based," eliminating the financial shock of unplanned downtime and optimizing inventory capital.
Slide 4: Module 3 – Benzene Safety (Winterization Guard)
The Problem: Benzene solidifies in pipelines at 5.5°C. Unpredictable winter cold snaps lead to extreme blockages, severe physical infrastructure stress, and expensive production halts. The AI/ML Architecture:

Model Used: Multivariate Regression Models.
The Advantage: Correlates localized meteorological forecasts with the physical thermodynamics of your exact pipes to predict freeze risks dynamically.
How it Works: Allows operators to route steam-tracing heat proactively, exactly where and when it's needed, rather than reacting to a blockage. Direct Client Value: Guarantees process continuity during adverse weather, preventing millions in physical damage while optimizing steam-tracing energy costs.
Slide 5: Module 4 – Flare & ESG Tracker (Regulatory Conformance)
The Problem: Unplanned process disturbances cause rapid flare drum surges, resulting in heavy regulatory fines, negative public relations, and the burning of valuable hydrocarbon products. The AI/ML Architecture:

Model Used: Time-Series Forecasting (ARIMA or LSTM Neural Networks).
The Advantage: Deep learning networks that recognize specific upstream pressure wave sequences that statistically precede a flare event.
How it Works: Provides operators a vital 30-minute predictive window to intervene and safely reroute the volatile gas via recycle valves. Direct Client Value: Avoids crippling ESG fines, improves institutional investor standing, and recovers volatile gas back into the system to be processed and sold—turning a liability into revenue.
